No. —, original.

Louisiana v. Cummins et al. October 27, 1941. Messrs. Eugene Stanley, Attorney General of Louisiana, and James J. Morrison were on the petition for rehearing. See ante, p. 577. Per Curiam:

The motion to strike Abraham L. Shushan, the citizen of Louisiana, as a party defendant is granted. The petition for rehearing is granted. Leave to file the complaint is denied. Massachusetts v. Missouri, 308 U. S. 1, 19-20.
